<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Pennisetum</i> <i>setaceum</i> or other <i>Pennisetum</i> species are dominant or co-dominant with other non-native species in the herbaceous layer. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1.5 m; cover is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Pennisetum </i>spp. > 50% relative cover in herbaceous layer (Keeler-Wolf and Evens 2006) and combined with other non-native plants > 90% relative cover.</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Steep coastal cliffs, bluffs, road-cuts, coastal dunes, coastal scrub, desert scrub types in areas with mild, frost-free winters.  </div>
</div>

        
